Haroni/Makurupini Forest between the Haroni R. & the Makurupini stream. Almost entirely in Rhodesia but the Makurupini rises in Mozambique. Situated at the foot of the wxtreme southern tip of the Chimanimani and therefore receives a much higher rainfall than is usual for this altitude in Rhodesia. Temperature high but cold winds & water come down from the mountain. For this reason, probably has some anomalous montane elements, i.e., Podocarpus milanjianus (stunted). Dominants: Parinari sp. near P. polyandra, Xelopia aethiopica, Funtumia latifolia, Newtonia buchananii, Blighia unijugata, Anthocleista grandiflora & Aporrhiza nitida.
